stylometry: An example of a probability distribution is triangular distribution. It is very popular because it is very simple to understand and explain. The results are formed in a triangular shape, with three points at the base of the triangle. The bottom point on the left hand side is point a, the minimum value. The bottom point on the right hand side is point b, the maximum value. Then draw a line from the top point of the triangle to the base, and thatis point c, or the most likely value. The triangular distribution can be symmetric or skewed to one side or another based on the information provided for the simulation model.
